rComments: A very kind and gentle personality, however I received one of my lowest English marks to date in her course. Too much focus on attendance (the sessions met 3 times a week. Great stimulating lectures but some of the texts chosen were extremely dry. Would love to see some fresh content in a Canadian lit course. Overall, okay.
Hard marker. Gives too many lecture hours and expects attendance 3 times a week. Nice person but she grades way to hard
Just make sure you sit at the front of the class where you can actually hear her.

Prof Kerber is the best prof Ive had in all 4 years of University. During lecture, she is clear, concise, sincere, and genuine, and still manages to incorporate student discussion. Outside lectures she is always willing to reply student emails, talk with them about the essay during office hours. She really cares about her students and you can tell.
Professor Kerber is a delightful professor. ENG382 is an invaluable course and she makes learning the sometimes difficult material easy.

Very dedicated prof who knows her subject material extremely well. Lectures append so much to the readings due to her knowledge of related material. Very kind, approachable; took the time to learn the names, first and last, of everyone in a class of over thirty within two months. Very personable.
She's amazing, approachable and very articulate. Class liked her so much she got a round of applause at the end of the year! Bravo!
Great Prof.  Can explain difficult concepts with clarity and appropriate examples.  Attentive to students questions.  She cares and it shows.
